			<ns0:name>cstefan...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/113511172007743761909/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">Make sure the release notes for Arctic reflect this:

Evgeniy: &amp;quot;Pepper functions can only be called from the main thread at the moment. First of all, this is not documented at all, and it is really confusing. Then, it considerably limits the SDL port. I had to initialize everything early, on request from the main thread, because all game actions happen on a non-main thread. Instead of pushing video frames from the game thread, I need either a paint() loop in JS or chained Flush() callbacks checking for frame availability.&amp;quot;</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2011-08-17T21:54:23.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2011-02-16T20:09:09.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:status>Fixed</ns2:status><ns2:owner>
